each of the R' substituents independently represents a substituent group selected from hydride, halide, a C1 -C8 alkyl group, a C3 -C12 alkylsilyl group, a C5 -C8 cycloalkyl group, a C6 -C10 aryl group, a C1 -C8 alkoxyl group, a C1 -C30 carboxylic group, a C2 -C10 dialkylamide group,


R" represents a substituent group of the same nature as the previous R' groups, independently selected from these, or a second anion containing an  ETA 5 -cyclopentadienyl ring co-ordinated to the titanium, and may also be covalently bound to A by means of a divalent bridged group, so as to form a cyclic structure comprising at least 4 atoms, one of which is the titanium atom;


"n" is equal to 1 or 2 respectively when the titanium is in oxidation state +3 or +4.

